Certainly! Below is a simple Java program that checks if a given word contains only vowels. We will then use this program to determine if any of the words "train", "sunshine", and "stepped" consist solely of vowels.

```java
public class VowelChecker {

    // Method to check if a word contains only vowels
    public static boolean isOnlyVowels(String word) {
        // Convert the word to lowercase to handle case insensitivity
        word = word.toLowerCase();

        // Loop through each character in the word
        for (char c : word.toCharArray()) {
            // Check if the character is not a vowel
            if ("aeiou".indexOf(c) == -1) {
                return false; // Return false if a non-vowel character is found
            }
        }
        return true; // Return true if all characters are vowels
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Words to check
        String[] words = {"train", "sunshine", "stepped"};

        // Check each word and print the result
        for (String word : words) {
            if (isOnlyVowels(word)) {
                System.out.println(word + " contains only vowels.");
            } else {
                System.out.println(word + " does not contain only vowels.");
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### Explanation:

1. **`isOnlyVowels` Method**: This method takes a word as input and checks each character to determine if it's a vowel. It uses the `indexOf` method to see if the character exists in the string "aeiou", which contains all the vowels. If any character is not a vowel, it returns `false`. Otherwise, it returns `true`.

2. **`main` Method**: This is where we test the function with the words "train", "sunshine", and "stepped". It iterates over each word, checks if it contains only vowels, and prints the result.

### Output:

This program will output:

```
train does not contain only vowels.
sunshine does not contain only vowels.
stepped does not contain only vowels.
```

As expected, none of the words "train", "sunshine", and "stepped" consist solely of vowels.
